<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>welcome to forge</title>
</head>
<body style="margin:0;padding:0;background-color:#0e0e0e;font-family:'Helvetica Neue',Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;">
  <table width="100%" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" border="0" style="background-color:#0e0e0e;">
    <tr>
      <td align="center" style="padding:40px 20px;">
        <table width="600" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" border="0" style="max-width:600px;width:100%;background-color:#1c1b1b;border-radius:12px;overflow:hidden;">

          <!-- top gradient bar -->
          <tr>
            <td style="background:linear-gradient(90deg,#ffb595,#ee671c);padding:4px 0;"></td>
          </tr>

          <!-- body -->
          <tr>
            <td style="padding:40px 40px 32px 40px;">

              <p style="margin:0 0 20px 0;font-size:16px;line-height:1.7;color:#a8a29e;">Heya builder!</p>

              <p style="margin:0 0 20px 0;font-size:16px;line-height:1.7;color:#a8a29e;">You just made it onto the Forge list, stoked to have you. 🔥</p>

              <p style="margin:0 0 20px 0;font-size:16px;line-height:1.7;color:#a8a29e;">My name is Aarav and I'm one of the lead organisers for Forge. Forge is where teen builders (13–18) get up to <span style="color:#ffb595;font-weight:600;">$2,000 in funding</span> to actually build the hardware they've been sketching in the margins of their notebooks. anything from PCBs, robots, 3D printed contraptions, custom keyboards, weird little gadgets. if you can solder it, print it, or wire it up, it belongs here.</p>

              <p style="margin:0 0 20px 0;font-size:16px;line-height:1.7;color:#a8a29e;">when the Forge fires up, you'll be one of the first through the doors. we'll send you early access to pitch your project and start building.</p>

              <p style="margin:0 0 12px 0;font-size:16px;line-height:1.7;color:#a8a29e;">until then here's some things you should totally do/checkout :)</p>

              <table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" border="0" style="margin:0 0 28px 0;width:100%;">
                <tr>
                  <td style="padding:6px 0;font-size:16px;line-height:1.7;color:#a8a29e;">
                    &bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href="https://hackclub.com/slack" style="color:#ffb595;text-decoration:none;">join the Hack Club Slack</a>
                  </td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td style="padding:6px 0;font-size:16px;line-height:1.7;color:#a8a29e;">
                    &bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;start thinking of your ideas. the best pitches come from ideas you're already obsessed with. doesn't need to be polished, just real.
                  </td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td style="padding:6px 0;font-size:16px;line-height:1.7;color:#a8a29e;">
                    &bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;shoot me a DM on Slack if you've got any questions (<span style="color:#ffb595;">@Aarav J</span>) on the HC Slack, or feel free to email me :D
                  </td>
                </tr>
              </table>

              <p style="margin:0 0 32px 0;font-size:17px;line-height:1.7;color:#e5e2e1;font-weight:600;">lets go forge something wild together!</p>

              <!-- divider -->
              <table width="100%" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" border="0" style="margin-bottom:24px;">
                <tr>
                  <td style="border-top:1px solid #2a2a2a;"></td>
                </tr>
              </table>

              <!-- signature -->
              <p style="margin:0;font-size:15px;line-height:1.8;color:#a8a29e;">
                Sincerely, The Forge Team<br>
                <a href="mailto:aarav@hackclub.com" style="color:#ffb595;text-decoration:none;">aarav@hackclub.com</a>
              </p>

            </td>
          </tr>

          <!-- bottom gradient bar -->
          <tr>
            <td style="background:linear-gradient(90deg,#ffb595,#ee671c);padding:4px 0;"></td>
          </tr>

        </table>
      </td>
    </tr>
  </table>
</body>
</html>
